ly generated metadata, which might be included in native and Right. However, I need to think about access coverage—specifically if resource access could exclude test resources. Instead of using test resources, I should consider using a library class resource. Should I remove the test resource? Maybe deleting it is better, but I can also edit the test. I'm also seeing that we shouldn’t broaden access unnecessarily. Removing the file might be necessary, and the test should call `fromResource` properly as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JCvdi7OGbuJqZMjPb7iiJTqv|fc_025771f99af579290169fb026c0398819daa6989a36651101d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm -f tests/src/dev.zio/zio-streams_3/2.1.16/src/test/resources/dev_zio/zio_streams_3/from-resource.txt && rmdir -p tests/src/dev.zio/zio-streams_3/2.1.16/src/test/resources/dev_zio/zio_streams_3 2>/dev/null || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 791, "output": 1129, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20864, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778057817488, "responseId": "resp_025771f99af579290169fb0259f724819db8fcbb3a7219f5c4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_JCvdi7OGbuJqZMjPb7iiJTqv|fc_025771f99af579290169fb026c0398819daa6989a36651101d", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778057839728}]}
